@base_url = http://localhost:8080


### 1. Create a contact
POST {{base_url}}/api/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Rakesh",
  "last_name": "K",
  "email": "rakesh@codersgyan.com",
  "tags": [
    { "text": "purchased:mern" },
    {"text": "purchased:devops"}
  ]
}

### 2. List all contacts
GET {{base_url}}/api/contacts

### 3. Add tags to a contact (via email)
POST {{base_url}}/api/contacts/tag
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "rakesh@codersgyan.com",
  "tags": [
    { "text": "joined:inner-circle" }
  ]
}

### 4. Remove a tag from a contact (by contact ID)
# Replace {id} with an actual contact ID from the list
PATCH {{base_url}}/api/contacts/1/tag
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "purchased:mern"
}

### 5. Create a campaign draft
POST {{base_url}}/api/campaigns
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Spring Sale 2026",
  "subject": "Our biggest sale is here!",
  "content": "<h1>Spring is here!</h1><p>Check out our new deals.</p>"
}

### 6. List all campaigns
GET {{base_url}}/api/campaigns

### 7. Get campaign details
# Replace {id} with an actual campaign ID
GET {{base_url}}/api/campaigns/1
